1. Information we collect
In order to provide better services, this application may collect the following types of information:
Personal information
When registering or using this application, you may need to provide some personal information, such as basic information such as email address, gender, age, weight, etc.
Device information
We may collect your device information, including device model, operating system version, device identifier, etc., to ensure the compatibility and performance of the application.
Log data
When you use this application, we will collect some log data (such as device logs, crash reports, etc.) to optimize application performance and solve technical problems.
Behavioral information
When you use this application, we will collect some information such as your clicks and page jumps in the application, which is only used to optimize application functions and enhance user experience.
2. How we use your information
Provide services
Provide personalized heart rate monitoring, health advice, data analysis reports and other services based on your health data.
Improve products and services
Based on user feedback and behavioral data, we continue to optimize application functions and user experience.
Security assurance
Protect your data from unauthorized access, modification or leakage to ensure the normal operation of the application.
3. Information Sharing and Disclosure
We promise not to sell your personal information to any third party. We may share your information with third parties in the following circumstances:
Legal requirements
We may disclose your information when required by law or by mandatory requirements of government agencies.
Service providers
We may work with third-party service providers to help us provide and improve the services of this application. We will ensure that these service providers strictly abide by the privacy protection agreement and access your information only to the extent necessary.
Business transfer
In the process of business mergers, acquisitions or asset transfers, your personal information may be transferred as one of the assets. We will notify you in advance and ensure that your privacy is protected.
4. Information security
We have taken reasonable technical and management measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, modification or destruction. This includes but is not limited to:
Data encryption technology to protect the transmission of sensitive data;
Access control mechanisms to limit access to user data;
Regular review and update of security measures.
Although we have taken these protective measures, please note that no security measures are foolproof and cannot guarantee that your information is completely secure on the Internet.
5. Your rights
You may exercise the following rights in accordance with applicable laws:
Access and correction
You can review and correct your personal information held by us and ask us to update or delete inaccurate information.
Data deletion
If you no longer wish to use this application, you can request the deletion of your personal information, unless we are legally obliged to retain it.
Withdrawal of consent
You have the right to withdraw previously given consent at any time, especially with regard to the processing of health data.
Data portability
If applicable, you have the right to request that we provide your personal information to you in a structured, commonly used format, or directly to another service provider designated by you.
6. Third-party services
This application may contain links to third-party websites or services. Please note that we are not responsible for the privacy policies of these third-party websites or services. We recommend that you read their privacy policies carefully before accessing these third-party services.
The following are third-party services used by this application:
Firebase
Admob
7. Updates to the privacy policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time to respond to changes in laws and regulations or adjustments to product features. We will notify you within the application and indicate the update date in the privacy policy. The updated Privacy Policy will be effective once posted.